  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 150°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grab a large Dutch oven or saucepan and set over a medium-high heat. Working in batches, brown the pork shoulder with a little sesame oil until lovely and golden brown. We’re looking to build really good flavour here, so take your time."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the red onion into chunky slices, finely slice the garlic and cut the ginger into matchsticks."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Whip the pork out of the pan and drop in the onions. Cook for 6-7 mins or until starting to wilt and sweat. Add the garlic and ginger along with the gochujang and cook for 5-6 mins. Add the pork back to the pan, add roughly chopped spring onions and cover with chicken stock. Add the soy and kimchi and bring to a boil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add a lid, leaving a slight gap and slide into the oven for 2.5-3 hours, or until the pork is super soft and the sauce has reduced."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Just before the ragú's ready, heat the rice according to the package instructions and briefly blanch the edamame beans."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Divide the rice between bowls and top with the ragu. Add edamame, kimchi and a little coriander. Add a sprinkling of sesame seeds and get stuck in with a delicious glass of Prestige Bordeaux Red by Calvet. Yum."
    }
  ],
